Dining table for an obese child: not breakfast and dinner nuts
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 have problems with overweight, with 9% of schoolchildren and 5% of obese children.
Obese children come from families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to a recent survey.
Again, it shows how important it is for the healthy development of the human environment in which it grows, and the patterns in which it is surrounded.
For example, on the tables of obese children, stools appear up to half as often as in the families of children with normal weight.
The fried potatoes had for dinner the day before the research related to a lighting event called Obesity is not a coincidence more than 19 percent of obese.
There is also no habit of sporting in thickets families, which, however, affects most of today’s schoolchildren’s families – only 15 percent of children answered that their parents would find time to actively move at least once a week.
A survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and attended at least 900 children from primary schools from all over the Czech Republic.
It was already the second year of the Obesity is not a coincidence that is supported by the General Health Insurance Company and Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 students from 4th to 8th grades have participated in the project.
Proper eating and enough exercise in the family is one of the determining factors that causes a dramatic increase in the number of children overweight or even obese.
“Only half of the respondents, for example, stated that they received five times a day in the breakfast-snack-snack-snack-dinner regime, which is one of the basic prerequisites for proper nutrition,” one of the results of the survey said.
No breakfast and no dinner for us
Experts note that for healthy development, there are also important and relative details, including, for example, the regular time of family breakfast.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of schoolchildren eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast on their own.
And the worst thing was the fact that in a dozen households don’t have breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the basis of a proper daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that in families with obese children, unhealthy potatoes are much more often consumed.
Almost everyone – regardless of weight – drinks sweet lemonade every day (70 percent).
Although more than 40 percent of the children surveyed regularly exercised, the result was less than half - 15 percent for their parents.
Set up your own Dining Room
The next part of the survey enabled the selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to make their own dining options according to their own taste and opinion.
"The nutritional preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15 are far from ideal in terms of healthy nutrition."
Among their favorite dishes are a lot of dairy, savory and sweet dishes.
“It’s especially alarming to have a huge taste for sweet lemonade,” the study’s final report said.
For lunch as the main meal, pasta was won just above the poultry.
However, children practically didn’t want to eat chickpeas at all, and the taste of fish and lunch vegetables is low.
Approach to Health
At the same time, the survey showed that children are willing to adjust their eating habits if they get the right information.
“In the control group of respondents who completed a questionnaire after the completion of the Obesity Lighting Lecture, there was no accident, in a number of cases a significant shift of preferences towards healthy nutrition principles,” the results of the project said.
This was notable, for example, for sweet lemonades, where more children would begin to prefer ordinary water.
Children also more often highlighted poultry and fish as the main meal of the day in the questionnaire and would limit sweet foods and toasts.
